<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-23T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="928" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d928">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 124.55/12a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-23T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>268. By direction of the President you are instructed to withdraw from
                            Belgium at once accompanied by the Legation staff, consular officers,
                            and all American members of the Commission for Relief in Belgium. Please
                            telegraph Department probable date of departure, route, and plans. You
                            should take up your official residence at Havre accompanied by your
                            Legation staff.</p>
                        <p>Before leaving you should carry out instructions contained in
                            Department’s 248, February 3, 5 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d928fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_630">p.
                                630</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>This Government has approved the proposal of the Netherland Government to
                            send into Belgium a certain number of Netherland subjects to undertake
                            the work thus far carried on by the American staff.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>